Help Type: command
Command: spinedigest queue

Purpose:
  Manage device-local generation tasks for `.sdpub` chapters.

Usage:
  spinedigest queue add <archive.sdpub> --chapter <id> --task <reading-graph|summary|knowledge-graph> --accept-cost [--boost] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>]
  spinedigest queue list [--all] [--active] [--input <archive.sdpub>]
  spinedigest queue status <job-id>
  spinedigest queue watch <job-id> [--jsonl] [--from beginning|now]
  spinedigest queue pause <job-id>
  spinedigest queue resume <job-id>
  spinedigest queue cancel <job-id>
  spinedigest queue boost <job-id>
  spinedigest queue target <job-id> --task <reading-graph|summary|knowledge-graph>
  spinedigest queue clean

Tasks:
  - reading-graph builds the reading-oriented chunk graph.
  - summary builds the summary path.
  - knowledge-graph builds entity/triple evidence.

Cost:
  Queue tasks may call an LLM, consume tokens, and incur provider charges.
  `queue add` requires `--accept-cost`.

Examples:
  spinedigest queue add book.sdpub --chapter 3 --task reading-graph --accept-cost
  spinedigest queue add book.sdpub --chapter 3 --task summary --accept-cost
  spinedigest queue watch <job-id> --jsonl
